com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.devices

Class DevicesRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<T>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.PaginatedRequestExecutor<Devices>
        • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.devices.DevicesRequestExecutor

  • public class DevicesRequestExecutor
extends PaginatedRequestExecutor<Devices>
    Request executor provided by DevicesApi. Use this class if you want to fetch devices through fluent API in chained fashion, for example: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   Devices devices = kontaktCloud.devices().fetch()
      .managerIds(managerId)
      .type(DeviceType.BEACON)
      .profile(DeviceProfile.IBEACON)
      .startIndex(5)
      .maxResult(10)
      .filter("major>=155")
      .execute();
